  • Method Details

    • getCustomCodes

      public static CustomPickerCode[] getCustomCodes(String[] parameters)
      Deprecated.
      please use a Gosu plugin or a Gosu library instead.
      Calls the custom picker adapter (actually a plugin) with the given string parameters and returns an array of custom picker codes which can be displayed using a Pebbles RowIterator.

      This is a deprecated interface and is only included for backward compatibility. Please use a Gosu plugin or a Gosu library instead.

      Parameters:
      parameters - the string parameters to the plugin. The interpretation of these depends on the customer's plugin implementation.
      Returns:
      an array of custom picker codes, each with a string code and string description. The exact contents of this array depends on the customer's plugin implementation.
      Throws:
      com.guidewire.pl.web.controller.UserDisplayableException - if there is an error in the plugin or an error communicating with the plugin. The exception is also logged to category Plugin.ICustomPickerAdapter.
